        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>B+ Tree Visualization</h1>

    <div class="controls">
        <div>
            <input type="number" id="keyInput" placeholder="Key" min="0">
            <button onclick="insertKey()">Insert</button>
            <button onclick="deleteKey()">Delete</button>
            <button onclick="searchKey()">Search</button>
            <button onclick="randomTree()">Random Tree</button>
            <button onclick="clearTree()">Clear</button>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-top: 10px;">
            <label>Order">Order (3-7):</label>
            <input type="number" id="orderInput" value="4" min="3" max="7" style="width: 40px;">
        </div>
    </div>

    <div id="treeContainer" class="tree-container"></div>

    <div class="explanation">
        <h3>B+ Tree Characteristics:</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>All keys are stored in the leaf nodes in sorted order</li>
            <li>Internal nodes only contain keys used for routing</li>
            <li>Leaf nodes are linked together for efficient range queries</li>
            <li>All leaves are at the same level</li>
            <li>Minimum keys: ceil(order/2)-1 in internal nodes, floor(order/2) in leaves</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Try inserting keys to see how the tree grows and splits. Notice how the tree remains balanced.</p>
    </div>

